    <!-- Add Activity -->
     <activity>
        <statement>
            <p>
                You are given the sequence <m>2, 6, 18, 54, ...</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Explore the sequence in your Groups to:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                <ol marker="(a)">
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the next two terms.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the common ratio.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Find the sum of the first four terms.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </p>
            <p>
                The sum of the first four terms is <m>80</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                To find this sum, consider;
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> a \amp = \; 2 </mrow>
                    <mrow> r \amp = \; 3 </mrow>
                    <mrow>S_4 \amp =\; 2 + 6 + 18 + 54 ........(i) </mrow>
                    <mrow> rS_4 \amp = \; r(2 + 6 + 18 + 54)  </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 3(2 + 6 + 18 + 54) </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 6 + 18 + 54 + 162 ........(ii) </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                Subtract (i) from (ii);
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> 3S_4 - S_4 \amp = \; 162 - 2 </mrow>
                    <mrow>\therefore S_4 \amp = \; \frac{160}{2} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \amp = \; 80 </mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                In groups find the sum of the first six terms of the sequence.
            </p>
            <p>
                In general, for a geometric sequence;
            </p>
            <p>
                First term <m> = a</m> and common ratio <m> = r</m>
            </p>
            <p>
                The sum of <m>n </m> terms is given by;
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> S_n =  \amp\; a + ar + ar^2 + ar^3 + ar^4 + ... + ar^{n-1} ........ (i) </mrow>
                    <mrow> rS_n \amp = \; ar + ar^2 + ar^3 + ar^4 + ar^5 + ... + ar^{n-1} + ar^n ......(ii) </mrow>
                    <mrow> rS_n - S_n \amp = \; ar^n - a </mrow>
                    <mrow> S_n(r-1) \amp = \; a(r^n-1) </mrow>
                    <mrow>S_n \amp = \; \frac{a(r^n-1)}{r-1}  ...........(*)</mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
            <p>
                <term>Alternatively:</term>
            </p>
            <p>
                We can subtract (ii) from (i) to give
            </p>
            <p>
                <md>
                    <mrow> S_n - rS_n \amp = \; a - ar^n</mrow>
                    <mrow> S_n(1 - r) \amp = \; a(1 - r^n) </mrow>
                    <mrow>S_n \amp = \; \frac{a(1 - r^n)}{1 - r}  ...........(**)</mrow>
                </md>
                
            </p>
        </statement>
     </activity>

